<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-05-02T13:05:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-05-02T13:05:00-05:00" n="717" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d717">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Swenson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Copenhagen</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-05-02T19:05:00+01:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 2, 1902, 7:05 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s memorandum Committee on Foreign Relations referred to in
                            Brun’s note to you April eighteenth may cause rejection treaty. Cable
                            explanation that will remove Danish Government objections, if
                            possible.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Swenson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>